  <Docs since="1">
    <summary>Shader is the base class for objects that return horizontal spans of colors
            during drawing.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Shader is the base class for objects that return horizontal spans of colors
            during drawing. A subclass of Shader is installed in a Paint calling
            paint.setShader(shader). After that any object (other than a bitmap) that is
            drawn with that paint will get its color(s) from the shader.</para>
      <para>
